id: pm-iktj
title: "Uniform stdin convention: every --*-file flag (body-file, close --reason-file, etc.) accepts '-' for stdin, matching the annotation --add - convention"
description: "Standardize stdin handling so every file-valued flag that accepts external content can use '-' for stdin, giving scripts and agents one predictable convention for generated bodies, reasons, and documents."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",composability
created_at: "2026-07-06T22:10:15.407Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T22:30:36.198Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: All file-reading flags across commands accept '-' to read stdin (inventory taken from contracts); behavior documented in the scripting contract (pm-psy1); error message for unreadable paths mentions the '-' option; tests cover piped heredoc usage; no behavior change for real paths
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-psy1,related,"2026-07-06T22:10:24.411Z",null,null
body: "Found in audit #15 follow-up: pm update --body-file - fails with ENOENT (tries to open a file literally named '-'), while pm notes --add - reads stdin. Agents composing bodies from heredocs/pipes (the grep/jq/heredoc composability principle) hit this asymmetry and fall back to temp files. Inventory every --*-file flag via pm contracts, route them through a shared read-file-or-stdin helper, and record the convention in the scripting contract. Related-not-duplicate: pm-kipd (GH-438 full-item JSON on stdin), pm-a2h3 (notes/learnings --stdin parity)."
